FROM (VALUES
  ('Timed Work Capacity Block', 'timed-work-capacity-block', 'Timed Work Capacity', 'A fixed-duration block where athletes accumulate quality work within a time domain using stations, rounds, or continuous effort under a clear time cap.', 'Organizes conditioning around a time cap so athletes learn pacing, density, and quality maintenance without chasing open-ended volume.', 'Work hard with good form for the set time. Rest when prescribed and keep quality high even as you get tired.', 'sustained work capacity and pacing under a time cap', ARRAY['density tolerance', 'repeatability', 'movement quality under fatigue', 'pacing'], 'timed_work_capacity', 'sustained_capacity', ARRAY['capacity', 'resilience', 'sustained_capacity'], ARRAY['output', 'movement_intelligence', 'prepare_and_access'], ARRAY['mixed', 'local_muscular_endurance', 'glycolytic'], '{"fatigue_intentional":true,"fatigue_level":"moderate","technical_risk_under_fatigue":"moderate","impact_risk_under_fatigue":"depends_on_exercises","grip_risk_under_fatigue":"depends_on_exercises"}', 'recommended', 'A timed block caps total session time and defines how work is organized inside that window — rounds, stations, or continuous work — with explicit quality expectations.', 'Time caps create controllable density, teach pacing, and prevent endless grinding while still building repeatability under fatigue.', 'Use late in session for Sustained Capacity when you want structured density with a clear end point. Works well for groups with a visible clock.', 'Do not use before Output or Movement Intelligence. Avoid when athletes lack baseline technique or when no time cap is defined.', ARRAY['running an open-ended block without a time cap', 'adding complex skills as fatigue rises', 'treating the block as a race regardless of form', 'using high-impact plyometrics under accumulating fatigue', 'no stop rules when quality collapses'], '{"default_prescription":{"beginner":{"minutes":6,"work_target_seconds":20,"rest_target_seconds"